.\"
.\" -------------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH BUGS
.\"
CHS-to-LBA conversion uses the geometry entered with the
.B g
command.
If the geometry does not match the actual drive the LBA fields will be
wrong.
Most XT-class BIOSes use only the CHS fields and ignore LBA entirely, so
this rarely causes a problem in practice, but modern tools that read the
LBA fields may report incorrect values.
.PP
The program does not validate that partition regions are non-overlapping
or that CHS end values are greater than CHS start values.
.\"
